       \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"draft\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2019-07-09\" who=\"#AA\">Alex Antoniou Epidoc editing and English translation\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode\u003C/change>\n            \t   \u003Cchange when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-20\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova added EDCS numbers\u003C/change>\n\t\t\u003Cchange when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography\u003C/change>\n\t    \u003Cchange when=\"2020-12-18\" who=\"#system\">Updated Zenodo DOI\u003C/change>\n            \t\u003Cchange when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references\u003C/change>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2022-10-31\" who=\"#martaf\">Marta Fogagnolo revised the text encoding, added dimensions, translations and commentary\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic001325_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic001325.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>Σοσίᾳ\u003C/name> \u003Cspace quantity=\"2\" unit=\"character\"/> \u003Cname>Ἐλάτῃ\u003C/name>\u003C/persName>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\"/>\u003Cw>γλυκυτάτῃ\u003C/w>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>Ἀφροδείσιος\u003C/name>\u003C/persName>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"4\"/>\u003Cw>σύμβιος\u003C/w>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>Text based on photographs\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"1-2\">\u003Cnote>Korhonen observes that the name of the deceased could be in the nominative form, but the presence of the attribute suggests that it is dative.\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                \u003Cp>To the sweetest Sosia Elate, Aphrodeisios, her husband.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"it\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                \u003Cp>Alla dolcissima Sosia Elate, Aphrodisios, il marito.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>The epitaph presents a less common structure, with the name of the deceased probably in dative and the name of the dedicant in nominative followed by an attribute that qualifies his relationship with the deceased (see Korhonen 2004: 87). To be excluded is the interpretation of the epitaph as two nominatives, the first of the name of the deceased, the latter of the name of the dedicant because of the attribute \u003Cforeign xml:lang=\"grc\">γλυκυτάτη\u003C/foreign>. The indication of the age of the deceased and the dedication verb is omitted. The gentilicium Sosia testifies that the deceased belonged the gens Sosia; her cognomen \u003Cforeign xml:lang=\"grc\">Ἐλάτη\u003C/foreign> is also attested in an inscription of imperial age from Dikaiarchia-Puteoli (CIL 10.2209). The name of the husband, \u003Cforeign xml:lang=\"grc\">Ἀφροδείσιος\u003C/foreign>, is well attested in several inscriptions of South Italy (LGPN 3A: 86).\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Gualtherus\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1624 [1625]\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>no.45\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/ZP8DE8KS\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Amico\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1741\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>246 no.1\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F5INCW3T\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002186\u003C/ref>\u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Torremuzza\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1769\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>142 no.43\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/SPTB56H3\"/>\n                    \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epi